"{\"abstract\":\"Ranking comments on an online news service is a practically important task for the service provider, and thus there have been many studies on this task. However, most of them considered users\\u2019 positive feedback, such as \\u201cLike\\u201d-button clicks, as a quality measure. In this paper, we address directly evaluating the quality of comments on the basis of \\u201cconstructiveness,\\u201d separately from user feedback. To this end, we create a new dataset including 100K+ Japanese comments with constructiveness scores (C-scores). Our experiments clarify that C-scores are not always related to users\\u2019 positive feedback, and the performance of pairwise ranking models tends to be enhanced by the variation of comments rather than articles.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"114276298\",\"name\":\"Soichiro Fujita\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/114276298\"},{\"authorId\":\"145111241\",\"name\":\"Hayato Kobayashi\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/145111241\"},{\"authorId\":\"144859189\",\"name\":\"M. Okumura\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144859189\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"114276298\",\"name\":\"Soichiro Fujita\"},{\"authorId\":\"1630410130\",\"name\":\"Hayato Kobayashi\"},{\"authorId\":\"144859189\",\"name\":\"M. Okumura\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1007/978-3-030-45442-5_17\",\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"71becf689650d29b43afaff37234d2718d0bfa60\",\"title\":\"Unsupervised Ensemble of Ranking Models for News Comments Using Pseudo Answers\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/71becf689650d29b43afaff37234d2718d0bfa60\",\"venue\":\"ECIR\",\"year\":2020}],\"corpusId\":196181642,\"doi\":\"10.18653/v1/P19-1250\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":true,\"is_publisher_licensed\":true,\"paperId\":\"81c23b7074afecaef54ca6a84c7e909f